=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;=
;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:150%;text-al=
ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">On Tuesday afternoon, I met my partner <strong>Julia Ioffe </strong>for=
 lunch at Le
Diplomate, Washington=E2=80=99s version of Balthazar, to welcome her back f=
rom her recent parental leave. Despite the various and seemingly incessant =
oscillations within the federal government and foreign policy community, th=
e town had an unmistakably ebullient, pre-cherry blossom season vibe=E2=80=
=94a reminder of how 60-degree weather can really lift spirits in late wint=
er. Either way, I couldn=E2=80=99t have been more excited to see my friend =
and colleague for the first time in months.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">We w=
ere sitting down to catch up, to commiserate over the global state of affai=
rs, and to plot her editorial direction in this brave new world. Julia, aft=
er all, has been the foremost chronicler of the Ukraine war and the most pe=
rspicacious journalist on the blob beat, with reportage that captures both =
the high-minded ambitions and the sharp-elbowed politics of the federal bur=
eaucracy.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:
0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Mere days before o=
ur meeting, of course, <strong>Donald Trump</strong>, <strong>J.D. Vance</s=
trong>, and <strong>Volodymyr Zelensky </strong>had staged their tragic, of=
f-script meeting at the White House=E2=80=94a cascade of unfortunate and ne=
arly surreal invective that could have been scripted by <strong>Armando Ian=
nucci</strong>. Julia had been focusing on a different target before Vance =
and Trump browbeat the Ukrainian leader about <em>their</em>
view of foreign diplomacy and Oval Office etiquette, but that plan was out =
the window by the time the meeting reached its denouement. As Zelensky exit=
ed the Oval, Julia switched gears and endeavored to capture the full scope =
of the fallout from that disastrous confab.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-=
bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">The first d=
raft of the piece hit my inbox on Monday morning and I dove right in. Natur=
ally, without fear or favor, Julia had surveyed top
opinion makers across town and unearthed a common leitmotif. While Democrat=
s were fulsome in their public praise of Zelensky, many grumbled privately =
that he had stepped on his own political rake amid this ostensible peace-ke=
eping summit. =E2=80=9CHe can be difficult, we know this,=E2=80=9D a former=
 senior <strong>Biden</strong> administration official told Julia. =E2=80=
=9CHe=E2=80=99s stubborn and he doesn=E2=80=99t take advice, and it=E2=80=
=99s really, really hard for him to think creatively. Everyone has these pr=
oblems; he just seems to
have a harder time hiding it than others.=E2=80=9D A Democratic foreign pol=
icy expert echoed the refrain. =E2=80=9CHe=E2=80=99s too arrogant,=E2=80=9D=
 this person told Julia. =E2=80=9CThinks that if he can only get face to fa=
ce with Trump, he can charm him. It never works. Not for Zelensky, not for =
<strong>Macron</strong>.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px=
;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">We published <a href=
=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0d=
WZGdDLTN5a1FhSERGVXI2RGZBcz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvZGVtb2NyYX=
RzLXByaXZhdGVseS1mdW1lLW92ZXItemVsZW5za3lzLW92YWwtb2ZmaWNlLXJvdy8_dXRtX2Nhb=
XBhaWduPVRoZStCYWNrc3RvcnkrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgzJTJGOCUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2=
dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9VGhlK0JhY2tzdG9yeSstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODMlMkY4JTJGMjUlMjl=
cdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3VzdG9tZXIuaW=
9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2YzYwNjE3Z=
GE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjIxMDMxNzN9/a2c58cf9d4ceda7b3c4f58eca164701a08f=
58f3624e8148c6367b6d0946ad1cf" style=3D"text-decoration:
underline;color:#d40000;"><em>Apr=C3=A8s Zelensky</em></a> on Monday evenin=
g. Almost immediately, Puck=E2=80=99s always percolating Slack channel was =
alight with notes from our partners, such as <strong>Matt Belloni </strong>=
and <strong>Marion Maneker</strong>, declaring that they=E2=80=99d been del=
uged with praise from friends and subscribers about the piece. On Tuesday a=
fternoon at Le Dip, I was thrilled to toast Julia=E2=80=99s success in pers=
on.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>The shapeshifting situation in
Europe is only becoming more complex. By Friday, of course, Trump threatene=
d sanctions on Russia=E2=80=94perhaps inadvertently taking Julia=E2=80=99s =
advice from her earlier piece, <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlb=
WFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dWZGdDLTN5a1FhSERGVXI2RGZBcz0iLCJocmVm=
IjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvdGhlLXRydW1wLXB1dGluLW5lZ290aWF0aW9ucy1hcmUtZG9=
vbWVkLXRoZXktYWx3YXlzLXdlcmUvP3V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1UaGUrQmFja3N0b3J5Ky0rU1VCU0=
NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MyUyRjglMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PVRoZStCYWNrc3RvcnkrL=
StTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgzJTJGOCUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rp=
b25cdTAwMjZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQ=
yYWJkMTJhIiwiaW50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjoyMDk0MD=
U0fQ/f9481b6c0e675d67c698826037ff5ee0cef7556d8b846cff7a23f265c9cfa4c1" styl=
e=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;"><em>The Fallacy of the Trump=
-Putin Pact</em></a>, to box in the strongman. Indeed, this is one of the g=
reat quagmires of our time, and it=E2=80=99s precisely what you should expe=
ct to read in Puck, as
narrated by the greatest interlocutor out there.</p></div>
